definition.value: A diterpene derived from pimarane by dehydrogenation across the  C(8)-C(14) and C(15)-C(16) bonds
A sesquiterpene derived from germacrane by dehydrogenation across the C(1)-C(10) and C(4)-C(5) bonds and cyclisation across the C(8)-C(9) bond.
A sesquiterpene that consists of (1S,5R)-2-methylbicyclo[3.1.0]hex-2-ene having a (2R)-6-methylhept-5-en-2-yl group attached at position 5.
A sesquiterpene that consists of (1S,5R)-2-methylbicyclo[3.1.0]hex-2-ene having a (2S)-6-methylhept-5-en-2-yl group attached at position 5.

A tetracyclic triterpenoid that is chrysene which has been fully hydrogenated except for a double bond between the 12 and 12a positions and which is substituted by methyl groups at positions 1, 1, 4b, 6a, 8 and 10a positions, and by a 4-methylpent-3-en-1-yl group at position 8 (the 2S,4aS,4bR,6aS,8R,10aR,10bS-diastereoisomer). It has been isolated from the root bark of the Panamanian tree Maytenus blepharodes.
A doubly-charged organophosphate oxoanion arising from deprotonation of the three diphosphate OH groups of 7-methylguanosine 5'-diphosphate(1+); major species at pH 7.3.
An organophosphate oxoanion arising from deprotonation of the three diphosphate OH groups of 8-oxo-dGDP; major species at pH 7.3.
A hydrate that is the monohydrate form of anhydrous tenovir.

An organic phosphonate that is the disoproxil ester of tenofovir. A prodrug for tenofovir, an HIV-1 reverse transcriptase inhibitor, tenofovir disoproxil is used as the fumaric acid salt in combination therapy for the treatment of HIV infection.
A fumarate salt prepared from equimolar amounts of tenofovir disoproxil and fumaric acid. It is used in combination therapy for the treatment of HIV infection.
A dicarboxylic acid dianion obtained by deprotonation of both carboxy groups of 3,3'-azobis(6-hydroxybenzoic acid) (olsalazine).
An EC 2.1.1.* (methyltransferases) inhibitor that interferes with the action of thymidylate synthase (EC 2.1.1.45).
An EC 2.1.2.* (hydroxymethyl-, formyl- and related transferases) inhibitor that interferes with the action of phosphoribosylglycinamide formyltransferase (EC 2.1.2.2).

An organic sodium salt that is the disodium salt of N-{4-[2-(2-amino-4-oxo-4,7-dihydro-1H-pyrrolo[2,3-d]pyrimidin-5-yl)ethyl]benzoyl}-L-glutamic acid. Inhibits thymidylate synthase (TS), 421 dihydrofolate reductase (DHFR), and glycinamide ribonucleotide formyltransferase (GARFT).

An organic sodium salt that is the heptahydrate form of pemetrexed disodium. Inhibits thymidylate synthase (TS), 421 dihydrofolate reductase (DHFR), and glycinamide ribonucleotide formyltransferase (GARFT).
A dicarboxylic acid dianion obtained by deprotonation of both carboxy groups of pemetrexed.
Any compound that can be used for the treatment of neurodegenerative disorders.
An amino acid zwitterion arising from transfer of a proton from the carboxy to the amino group cis-4-hydroxy-L-proline; major species at pH 7.3.
A purine 2'-deoxyribonucleoside 5'-diphosphate having 8-oxoguanine as the nucleobase.
A guanosine 5'-phosphate that consists of guanosine 5'-diphosphate bearing a 7-methyl substituent and having a negatively charged diphosphate group.
A C-glycosyl compound that is 9H-xanthen-9-one substituted by hydroxy groups at positions 1, 3, and 7 and a 1,5-anhydro-D-glucitol moiety at position 1.
A guanosine 5'-phosphate that consists of guanosine 5'-diphosphate bearing a 7-methyl substituent.
A pimarane diterpenoid resulting from the oxidation of primary alcohol group of 9beta-pimara-7,15-dien-19-ol to the corresponding carboxylic acid.
Any alcohol in which two hydroxy groups are bonded to the same atom.
A 1,1-diol resulting from the formal addition of water to the carbonyl group of a aldehyde.
A 1,1-diol resulting from the formal addition of water to the carbonyl group of a ketone.
A monocarboxylic acid that is (2Z,4E)-hexa-2,4-dienoic acid in which the hydrogen at position 2 is replaced by a hydroxy group.
A diadenosyl polyphosphate that consists of two adenosinyl moieties bridged by a hexaphosphate.
A diadenosyl polyphosphate that consists of two adenosinyl moieties bridged by a pentaphosphate.
A diadenosyl polyphosphate that consists of two adenosinyl moieties bridged by a tetraphosphate.
A diadenosyl polyphosphate that consists of two adenosinyl moieties bridged by a triphosphate.
An organophosphate oxoanion obtained by global deprotonation of the hexaphosphate OH groups of P(1),P(6)-bis(5'-adenosyl)hexaphosphate

A dioxo monocarboxylic acid that consists of hydrindane bearing two oxo substituents at positions 1 and 5, a methyl substituent at position 7a and a 2-carboxyethyl substituent at position 4 (3aS,4S,7aS-diastereomer).
A 3-hydroxy-5,9,17-trioxo-4,5:9,10-disecoandrosta-1(10),2-dien-4-oic acid that has 1E,2Z geometry.
A dTDP-sugar having 3-acetamido-3,6-dideoxy-alpha-D-galactopyranose (3-amino-3-deoxy-alpha-D-fucopyranose) as the sugar component.
A glycine derivative whose structure comprises a glycine core carrying an N-[5-(p-nitrobenzyloxy)-5-oxopentanoyl] substituent.
A glycine derivative whose structure comprises a glycine core carrying an N-[5-(p-nitrophenoxy)-5-oxopentanoyl] substituent.
A cyclic hydroxamic acid that consists of 1,4-benzoxazine bearing three hydroxy substituents at positions 2, 4 and 7 as well as an oxo group at position 3.
A monocarboxylic acid amide  compound having an N-(5-carboxypentyl) substituent and a C-[4-(4-nitrophenoxy)-4-oxobutyl)] substituent.
An N-acylglycine whose structure comprises a glycine core carrying an N-(4-{hydroxy[(4-nitrobenzyl)oxy]phosphoryl}butanoyl) substituent.

A monocarboxylic acid that is prop-2-enoic acid which is substituted at position 2 by a 4,7-dimethyl-1,2,3,4,4a,5,6,8a-octahydronaphthalen-1-yl group (the 1S,4R,4aS,8aR diastereoisomer). It is a sesquiterpenoid precursor of artemisinin, obtained from sweet wormwood, Artemisia annua.
A diterpenyl phosphate that is the O-diphospho derivative of (5S,9S,10S,13E)-labda-7,13-dien-15-ol.
A class of galactoglycerolipids that consists of any 1,2-diacyl-sn-glycerol having an alpha-D-galactosyl residue attached at position 3.
A 1,2-diacyl-3-alpha-D-galactosyl-sn-glycerol in which the groups at the 1- and 2-positions are both palmitoyl.
A ferrocene complex in which one of the cyclopentadienyl rings is substituted with a dimethylcarbamoyl group while the other carries a 4-carboxybutanamido group.
A 1,2-diacyl-3-alpha-D-galactosyl-sn-glycerol in which the groups at the 1- and 2-positions are both oleoyl.
